<br>
Justice Shaman of the Everfrost
<br>
<b><font color="#00CCFF"> Proud Member of Sacred Valor, Lanys T'vyl</font></b></center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/ulittleniffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LittleNiffo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 134<br> <font color=#8B4513>(3/14/01 1:07:26 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.fbe.unsw.edu.au/staff/graham.hannah/eq/resources/niffo60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /wave</span><hr size=1> Hi Ho,<br>
<br>
thanks for swinging by, I think we could sure use your help doing raids at some point. It seems to be a complicated tricky thing to have it go smoothly for all the characters that turn up.<br>
<br>
So I am glad you came by - I am sure we can pick your brain  :-)<br>
 <p><font color="#FF3333">Feet be well,<br>
Niffo.</font> </p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uwarninwraithlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warnin Wraithlore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/sig.JPG BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 255<br> <font color=#8B4513>(3/14/01 4:31:29 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/warnin1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /wave</span><hr size=1> Sanedin, as Niffo said there are many areas in which we could probably use your help.  Right now we are just learning and trying different things out.  Many of us are learning grouping tactics and our chosen character classes and all that still.  We are a ways away from having a full blown raid on a zone.  However, I have been planning a mini-raid in my head for Najena.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Once it is attempted you will see a striking resemblence to the raids you have planned for Sacred Valor, as I am pretty much using your model.<br>
<br>
That is a little bit off in the future though.  I still would love your help.  Maybe we could plan a joint low-level raid with Sacred valor having them join us with their secondaries.  Another idea is that you lead us on a raid and we all pay very close attention on how you lead it so we get to learn better.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Our biggest problem when planning these things is that about 10-12 of our 15-17 members are in australia.  That is a 17 hour time difference (into the future) with Pacific Standard Time (PST).  Those in australia have a regular playing time that is 11:00pm PST on Thursdays.  I have been unsuccessful for the most part in coaxing a group of them out at any other time.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Which is understandable considering good times for us either place them at work or in the middle of the night.<br>
<br>
Anyway, we'll definately keep in contact and maybe we can work something out.<br>
<br>
be well friend! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uthetalesinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Talesinger </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#8B4513>(3/14/01 8:52:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Raid?</span><hr size=1> <br>
If anyone needs any ideas on raiding the numerous booze houses in Freeport fell free to send me a tell. I have quite a bit of experience in it. Be forewarned, it can be a dangerous undertaking, but the rewards are well worth the effort.<br>
<br>
~Talesinger <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/ulittleniffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LittleNiffo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#8B4513>(3/14/01 2:03:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.fbe.unsw.edu.au/staff/graham.hannah/eq/resources/niffo60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid?</span><hr size=1> Hi Ho,<br>
<br>
- follows taly blindly on booze raid only to be struck with a 4 hour drunken corpse recovery    <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As for Friday Night Sydney time - Sorry it has become so entrenched here Warnie - I am sure some of the guys will be available at other times maybe we should work on another regular time as well.... <p><font color="#FF3333">Feet be well,<br>
Niffo.</font> </p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uwarninwraithlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warnin Wraithlore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/sig.JPG BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 260<br> <font color=#8B4513>(3/14/01 5:24:09 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/warnin1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid?</span><hr size=1> LOL Talesinger.  I'm in!  Hehe, the first thing Talesinger did after saying hi when I met him was give me alcohol.  I loved it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As for the time thing I am sorry if it came off the wrong way.  Was trying to explain it to Sanedin.  It is an obstacle we will learn to overcome.  Once we get more north american members we will be able to have 2 regular playing times (not necessarily a week) so it won't be so hard.  That will give everyone more options on whihc times they can attend and such.  I think for the most part any weekly gatherings will be on a small scale, it will be hard to organize a big thing for every week .  The big raids and events will be less often, which is a good thing because they would start to interfere with regualr game time of those who plan them.  That and they get to be less exciting if you do them all the time.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I was just explaining it not complaining about it.<br>
<br>
be well!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/ugumbrils.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gumbrils</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#8B4513>(3/14/01 5:32:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.fbe.unsw.edu.au/staff/graham.hannah/eq/resources/gumbrils60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid?</span><hr size=1> Yes, timing is a nuisance. I vote that all our overseas guild members should take a trip to Australia some time, just so that you can be in room with us all at the Friday night session (hey it should be pretty cheap for you guys, an Australian dollar should be worth about 2 American cents sometime in the next couple of days at the current rate of descent - though I don't know how we compare with the Canadian dollar).<br>
<br>
On a slightly more realistic note, if something was organised on the occasional Sunday morning/afternoon here in Sydney (my feeble understanding is that 2pm on Sunday in Sydney is about 7pm Sat PST) then maybe we would have a quorum of Sydney people able to play as well. Personally, I don't think that Kate (the evil Mattila) and I could do that every week, but once a fortnight or once every three weeks should be manageable, especially with some advance warning. Is that a reasonable time for our members not in Australia?<br>
<br>
Gumbrils<br>
